 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/utelkandoretelenesis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Telkandore Telenesis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t board camper</span><br>  Posts: 380<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/4/02 6:58:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1284.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Legendary</span><hr size=1> You make good points Mr. Fabmatil. My &quot;How dare you Verant!&quot; attitude blinded me of those facts.<br>
<br>
But, I still smell something fishy here. I know Verant was juggling around the idea of a premium type server long ago. They had one of those polls I remember, that asked if anyone would pay more for a premium type server with extra CS and other things. They didn't release the results I don't think, but from getting opinions on it myself in game and on the boards, it seemed the popular opinion was &quot;Nope&quot;.<br>
<br>
It's a risky thing for Verant to do if they're in need of more money, and with the ton of money I'm sure they're putting into setting it up, it could turn into something very bad if the plan fails. A move they knew would be very unpopular, that has a good chance to not work out... I dunno, just doesn't seem right <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/unjialstormcaller.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Njial Stormcaller</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t board camper</span><br>  Posts: 158<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/4/02 8:34:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1284.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Legends Server</span><hr size=1> This is really just a consumer confidence issue. Most ppl dont have the confidence that VI will do this right. I mean if they couldn't do this kind of stuff when they have been promising it for over 2 years now, what makes anybody think its gonna happen now, regardless how many people they hire or how much they charge. Personally I'm of the opinion that they should have just offered to do this for everyone for an extra $5-10. I think most people would pay that just for the increased CS and the map feature. If the dynamic content is near what they said it would be like, i think most ppl would definitely would come up with the $$$, not 30 extra, but 10 would be ok. I mean the whole thing is kinda like with Microsoft. They come out with a new OS, yah its gonna have some new cool stuff, but its still gonna crash on your randomly, so forth and so on, so most ppl are hesistant to upgrade. Someone on one of the posts, not sure if its on this board or not, compared it to digital cable vs. regular cable. Thats not exactly a fair comparison, as both are pretty much bug free services. A more accurate one would be asking someone to upgrade to digital cable, when the cable they have now, a 1/4th of the channels cut out intermittently, some of your favorite shows, the cable company just stops showing, and you get a horrible signal.  <p><center><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=46665>
