<br>
  In all businesses the main thing you must know is what is considered a reasonable price for your product. To be honest, EQ is probably a bit under priced , but $40 a month might be a little overpriced. They can find out a little by polling the customer base, but the only way to be sure is by actually implementing it.<br>
<br>
  I hope the new server is a success , I wouldn't play on it, but the more revenue that they can derive from online gaming, the more money they can devote to it, which hopefully will allow us to see better more involved games *with* decent CS. I would hate to think that EQ, as good as it is , is the height of what online gaming will be.<br>
<br>
  I also expect EQ to probably increase subscription rates by about 20% this year, it doesn't look like their customer base is increasing any and they will want to show an increase in revenue so realistically they should raise the rates. They could probably double the charge and still maintain over half their customers and cut their costs in half, when EQ starts declining that is what they will do.<br>
