<br>
Economically speaking, $10/month is very inexpensive.  Before I began playing EQ, I would spend maybe $75-100 dollars/month for games (a conservative number), because I like to play games.  Since I began playing EQ, I have purchased exactly ZERO other games.  I have a couple games I can play when my ISP is fuxored, but I play EQ exclusively.<br>
<br>
VI/Sony hasnt raised thier rates at all since day 1, mostly because the subscriber base continued to grow.  But now as player populations begin to plateau, they need a way to generate more revenue in order to remain competitive.  Have they outlasted every other MMORPG? All indications say yes, but as newer games begin to emerge which are superior to EQ (DAOC is still a contender for that honor), the current pricing model they have + stagnant player populations = EQ loses.<br>
<br>
I'm sure they did some kind of risk study to see what would happen if they jacked up monthly fees to, say, $15.  How many people would they lose? Maybe they decided it wasn't worth the risk.  They took a target revenue figure, juggled some numbers, and came up with the Legends Server.  It satisfies the needs/desires of a certain cross-section of the EQ population, and it makes them money.  If only 50 people from each existing server left and went over to Legends, well....thats 2000 people on Legends.  Not that hard to suck in what amounts to 0.5% of thier player-base, IMHO.<br>
<br>
They have been trying to satisfy various player-types and demands and been fairly successful.  This is another reason why EQ has such wide appeal.  Hard-core PvP?  Got it.  Team-based PvP? Cross-server events? Character Transfers? Role-playing? UK Subscribers? Yep.  Sure, it would be great if they offered the Legends server for $10/month, but since they are adding so much more content and bells and whistles, it *should* be more...<br>
<br>
$40/month is a lot of money, but has anyone looked at the proposed price points for up-and-coming 'EQ-killers?'  Some of the numbers being kicked around for SWG, City of Heroes, et. al. are around $12.99-$18, and I've even heard rumors that SWG will be more in the $20+/month range (Gotta pay Lucas for that licencing fee <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )  And I bet you that they wont offer the kinds of services VI is offering with the Legends package.  You will pay to play and that's it...<br>
<br>
I'm not paying $40/month to start from scratch again.  That's MY bottom line.  But people WILL pay this money, and if it doesn't pay for *our* (read: non-Legends subscribers) EQ, well, then I'm sure it will pay for the development/R&amp;D for EQ2.  And that is a good thing. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=65044"><b><i>Kromagnon</b></i></a><br>51 Champion of Vis Veres<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=64070"><b><i>Keldomahge Sayvray</b></i></a><br>52 Wanderer of Conspiracy<br></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=1284.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=1284.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=1284.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1284.topic&index=34><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=1284.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm1.threadControl?topicID=1284.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1284.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthet